"artefacts that can be reproduced locally (caches, build outputs, "
"packaging directories), virtual environments that are machine-specific, "
"test files that are not needed at runtime, and Flower's own internal "
"directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-to-configure-pyproject-toml.rst:242
msgid ""
"If you use ``fab-include`` to add a file that does not match any of the "
"built-in include patterns (for example, a ``.txt`` file), Flower will "
"raise an error and list the conflicting files. The fix is to remove those"
" patterns from ``fab-include``. Files that *do* match the built-in "
